Well since this is the bar I’ve spent the most time in, I should give it a real review.  It is by far my favorite bar for a variety of reasons. It is unpretentious and even though there’s sometimes a line, you will eventually get inside.  The bartenders are hot, especially when they bring in the night shift, some of the hotter girls working on Hubbard in my opinion.  The security staff is no joke and that’s because they have to be. The element that comes in here can be borderline criminal at times, or just outright obnoxiously drunk. Boss bar serves as a sieve that filters out the drunkards that endlessly stream down Hubbard, it’s massive neon sign serving as a calling beacon for the zombie-eyed blackout. And they let them in, until 4 am (and 5 am on Saturdays).  Reasonably priced drinks, and no snottiness, which is rare for Hubbard. And believe it or not, edible food, it’s actually not that bad. If you want to have fun you can come here and do it, you can make out behind the Golden Tee machine, stomp, sit in the windows or get in a fight over a game of pool. There’s a bouncer assigned to the pool table specifically to keep people from fighting over games.  The bathrooms are always a mess by 2 am. One toilet is clogged from puke/poop and there’s multiple broken beers on the ground, I feel sorry for those janitors. This is the only bar in Chicago where I have actually witnessed people having sex in the bathrooms, and I’m pretty sure they finished (no bathroom attendants).  And although some sketchy things have been known to go down here it is by far one of the most diverse bar crowds you can find ranging from construction workers, after work yuppies, tourists, gold coast silver foxes and everything in between.  Everyone has their one memorable experience at boss bar and if you don’t have that “bad decisions at boss bar story” then you aren’t really from Chicago.
